FBIS4-42213 "drweu105_g_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-105 Daily Report 31 May 1994 CANADA Military Communications Specialists To Leave for Rwanda Military Communications Specialists To Leave for Rwanda LD3105141694 Montreal Radio Canada International in English 1330 GMT 31 May 94 LD3105141694 Montreal Radio Canada International English BFN [Text] Canada has decided to send 300 forces' communications specialists to Rwanda. Defense Minister David Collenette says their deployment depends on the United Nations supplying 5,500 peacekeeping troops. Mr. Collenette says the Canadian soldiers stationed in Kingston, Ontario, have been warned to be ready to ship out for a six-month assignment. Only a few Canadians are now stationed with the UN force in Rwanda, including the group's commander, Major General Romeo Dallaire.
